description: India has lost the top buyer status of sea-borne Russian oil to China as sanctions fears grow. China has surpassed India in seaborne crude imports with 1.82M barrels daily vs. 1.36M. Indian refiners are rejecting Russian cargoes due to sanctions on ships, enabling China to enjoy heavily discounted deals.

description: Former Congress leader Sanjay Nirupam faced expulsion from the party due to alleged "indiscipline" and "anti-party statements," following the party's decision to relinquish the Mumbai North West Lok Sabha seat to Uddhav Thackeray's party. description: NATO on Thursday marks 75 years since its founding with the Western alliance confronted by the urgent need to do more to help Ukraine win a war currently roiling Europe.  Since Russia launched its all-out invasion of Ukraine two years ago, a reinvigorated NATO has added Finland and Sweden to its ranks and bolstered its forces in eastern Europe.
